PROMPT oracle_bone_bronze_relationship
WITH BUDGET 6000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a Chinese paleography and archaeology expert specializing in early Chinese writing systems, Shang and Zhou dynasty inscriptions, and the evolution of Chinese characters from oracle bone script through bronze inscriptions.")

GENERATE
    explain_relationship("Explain the relationship between oracle bone script (甲骨文 jiǎgǔwén) and bronze inscriptions (金文 jīnwén). Cover: 1) The chronological relationship showing oracle bone script as primarily Shang dynasty (c. 1250-1046 BCE) and bronze inscriptions as spanning late Shang through Western Zhou (c. 1046-771 BCE) and beyond, 2) The evolutionary connection demonstrating how bronze inscriptions developed from oracle bone script as the writing system transitioned from divination contexts to ceremonial and commemorative purposes, 3) Comparative analysis of character forms showing how oracle bone pictographs evolved into the more standardized and stylized bronze inscription characters, 4) The functional differences between oracle bones used for divination and royal record-keeping versus bronze vessels used for ritual ceremonies, ancestral worship, and commemorative purposes, 5) How bronze inscriptions expanded the content scope from mainly divination queries to include detailed historical records, genealogies, land grants, military achievements, and ceremonial dedications, 6) The technical differences in inscription methods from carving on bone to casting or engraving on bronze, and how this affected character development, 7) The social and political context showing how bronze inscriptions reflected the Zhou dynasty's need to legitimize their rule and document feudal relationships, 8) Specific examples of character evolution from oracle bone to bronze inscription forms, 9) How both writing systems contributed to the continuous development of Chinese characters leading to later scripts like seal script (篆書), 10) The scholarly significance of studying both systems together for understanding early Chinese civilization, political structures, religious practices, and the unbroken tradition of Chinese writing.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 3000 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.1, FORMAT markdown;